        },
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> > But in order for the lsp to work properly, it should be populated with this \"shape\", i dont know whats your opinion on providing a default implementation for this\r\n> \r\n> if nvim-lspconfig can provide a reasonable default, then it should ðŸ‘\r\n> \r\n> should probably leave that for a separate PR though.\r\n\r\nAgree, i currently have this implementation for populating init_options, which is working well. However i noticed that when i change to a new worktree, then i get warnings just like the language server was not properly configured. I realized it is because, each time i change worktree (change directory) the lsp is not reinitialized with the new init_options, concretely the 'workspace_path' pointing to the new worktree dir\r\n\r\nI am unsure about how to deal with this, i am not quite familiar with lua/lsp, but i am keen on contributing, even if it's with little PR's like this one\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nM.get_gh_actions_init_options = function(org, workspace_path, session_token)\r\n\torg = org or \"my-org\"\r\n\tworkspace_path = workspace_path or vim.fn.getcwd()\r\n\tsession_token = session_token or os.getenv(\"GH_TOKEN\")\r\n\r\n\tlocal function get_repo_name()\r\n\t\tlocal handle = io.popen(\"git remote get-url origin 2>/dev/null\")\r\n\t\tif not handle then\r\n\t\t\treturn nil\r\n\t\tend\r\n\t\tlocal result = handle:read(\"*a\")\r\n\t\thandle:close()\r\n\t\tif not result or result == \"\" then\r\n\t\t\treturn nil\r\n\t\tend\r\n\t\t-- Remove trailing newline\r\n\t\tresult = result:gsub(\"%s+$\", \"\")\r\n\t\t-- Extract repo name from URL\r\n\t\tlocal repo = result:match(\"([^/:]+)%.git$\")\r\n\t\treturn repo\r\n\tend\r\n\tlocal repo_name = get_repo_name()\r\n\r\n\tlocal repo_info = fetch_github_repo(repo_name, session_token, org, workspace_path)\r\n\treturn {\r\n\t\tsessionToken = session_token,\r\n\t\trepos = {\r\n\t\t\trepo_info,\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t}\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\n```",
